{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772117730,"nonce":"KUblRcMAATzvVJYMbvLvidemCow=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87uLpUozwAAAAVhP-TK"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772124437,"nonce":"Rh49TvhcajnS36NIEommxWRDLo8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sgEfw","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/276#issuecomment-3967830000"},"message":"## Design note: handling Copilot review false positives\n\nObserved during PR #285: Copilot flagged \"Only what's needed\" as not matching the canonical principle name \"Radical simplicity\" — but PR #283 had already renamed it. Copilot was comparing against a stale view of `main`.\n\n### Pattern for the review-pr skill\n\nWhen the review-pr skill evaluates Copilot review comments alongside its own findings:\n\n1. **Check for stale-base false positives** — if the branch was created before a recent merge to `main`, Copilot may flag things that are already resolved. The skill should note when a Copilot comment appears to reference stale state.\n\n2. **Reply to false positives with explanation** — leave a reply on the comment explaining why it's incorrect. This creates a paper trail for human reviewers.\n\n3. **Thumbs-down false positives** — use the GitHub reactions API (`-1` on the comment) to signal to Copilot that the feedback was unhelpful.\n\n4. **Note limitation**: Copilot docs confirm that dismissing or resolving comments does **not** prevent Copilot from repeating them on re-review. The real lever for recurring false positives is `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (see #286).\n\n### API patterns\n\n```bash\n# Reply to a review comment\ngh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr}/comments/{comment_id}/replies \\\n  -X POST -f body=\"Explanation of why this is a false positive\"\n\n# Thumbs-down a comment\ngh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/comments/{comment_id}/reactions \\\n  -X POST -f content=\"-1\"\n```\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772125115,"nonce":"7moLhSChv/msRfSpkmYeO56qfX4=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sgV-9","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/276#issuecomment-3967901629"},"message":"## Design note: requesting Copilot re-review and tracking review status\n\n### Requesting re-review programmatically\n\nAfter fixing Copilot review comments, the agent can request a re-review via the API:\n\n```bash\ngh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr}/requested_reviewers \\\n  -X POST -f 'reviewers[]=copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]'\n```\n\nNote: the `[bot]` suffix is required. This should be part of the completion step — after addressing review comments, push fixes and request re-review.\n\n### PR review status dashboard\n\nA pain point exists around finding PRs that need attention across the repo:\n- Which PRs have unresolved Copilot comments?\n- Which PRs had comments addressed but haven't been re-reviewed?\n- Which PRs are clean and ready for human review?\n\nThe review-pr skill could support a triage/dashboard mode (no PR argument) that scans open PRs and reports their review status. This would replace the primitive keyword-matching in `status_report.sh --pr-triage` with something that actually reads review state.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772126297,"nonce":"Aae01wJ0XqCnrkHqVh8bZkMM0lU=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sg0uQ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/276#issuecomment-3968027536"},"message":"## Triage Report\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** The core skill is clear, but design notes already on this issue have expanded scope to four features:\n1. Per-principle evaluation of a specific PR (original)\n2. Copilot false positive handling\n3. Copilot re-review triggering\n4. PR dashboard/triage mode\n\nRecommend starting with #1, including #2-3 as natural extensions, deferring #4.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | **Watch** | Scope creep risk — start with core evaluation |\n| A change includes its consequences | **Action needed** | Removing `--pr-triage` from `status_report.sh` also requires updating: Makefile `pr-triage` target, `.claude/skills/make_pr-triage/` skill, help text |\n| Capture decisions | OK | Design notes on this issue capture Copilot patterns |\n| Workspace improvements cascade to projects | OK | Evaluates both workspace and project PRs |\n\n### Cleanup Blast Radius\n\nThe `--pr-triage` removal is larger than expected:\n- `status_report.sh`: ~100 lines (keyword classification + triage output)\n- `Makefile`: `pr-triage` target\n- `.claude/skills/make_pr-triage/`: generated skill\n- Any docs referencing `--pr-triage`\n\n### Design Questions\n\n1. **Report destination**: Issue says \"structured report\" but not where. Lifecycle pattern from #282 suggests: output in conversation, user decides whether to post as PR comment.\n\n2. **Copilot interaction scope**: Should the skill automatically reply to false positives and thumbs-down them? Or just report findings and let the user/implementer act? Suggest: report + recommend, act only with explicit user approval.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Initial skill scope: evaluate a single PR, produce report in conversation\n- Include Copilot false-positive detection as a natural extension\n- Dashboard mode → separate issue or documented future addition\n- Verify full cleanup list before implementation\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772126436,"nonce":"OVeqazsGZay+a34sjO69PuG0N0s=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sg4uJ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/276#issuecomment-3968043913"},"message":"Regarding scope, should we limit this to 1 to review the pr, and have a triage pr skill for 2-3? Is so, we could open a separate issue for that.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772142620,"nonce":"UptAjAN7/ZBHwbXhSxLxm5pI2BY=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uLpUozwAAAAVh8poK"},"status":2}]}